Introduction

Kandis is a South Korean girl group under SXTYDGRS. The group consists of four members: Hello, Venny, Nine and Looky

On January 1, 2022, Hello was revealed as Kandis' first member. Nine was later revealed on January 8 as the group's second member.

Originally a duo, they made their debut on August 27, 2023, with the single album "BF".

On October 10, 2023, it was announced that a new member, Venny, will be joining Kandis. They released their second single album "Weed Out", marking Venny's debut, on October 23.

On January 30, 2024, a fourth member was teased. On August 22, 2024 it was revealed that Looky is the fourth and final member of Kandis. At the same time, it was announced that Kandis revealed their official fandom name to be "Gummis" and that they release their first full-length album, Playground, in January 14, 2025.
